race.comment: WESTBOUND (12) debuts with a top metro hoop sticking from the recent trial win at Lark Hill. Draws a bit awkwardly but he looks to have good ability. The yard is flying and this is a winnable assignment. CANTILEVER (1) switched barns and resumed with a solid run before improving again over this trip beaten 2.25L after being in the firing line on the corner. Is still well shy of his best and has strong prospects. MR UNIVERSE (2) was only beaten 2L at Belmont at big odds before a 1.5L defeat at Toodyay. Has the inside gate and can gets into the finish. BLACK CILLA (10) did a big job narrowly beaten from the back first up at big odds over a shorter sprint. On that effort the extra metres won't bother but she has to hold the form.
